main event: A witness reported seeing two flying saucers over Oxford, Ohio, on November 5, 1955.
interesting points: The objects were circular in shape and appeared much larger than stars,The objects were about twice as bright as a star,The sighting lasted for approximately 10-15 minutes,The witness initially thought the objects were airplanes but realized they were not,The objects were spotted at an angle of about 50 to 70 degrees from the witness's position.
witness description: The witness was walking down College Avenue after visiting a friend.
